Direct Brands is looking for creative, ambitious, and versatile Product Managers to join our team. For nearly a century, Book-of-the-Month, Columbia House, Doubleday, and our 21 enthusiast clubs have represented the largest media club businesses in the U.S. Nearly every book, movie, and music fan can remember getting &quot;10 CDs for a penny&quot; or &quot;4 books for a dollar&quot; at some point in their lives. Today, we are hard at work building an innovative media business positioned at the intersection of ecommerce, content, and online communities. This transformation will require leaders who move fast, possess an entrepreneurial spirit required to break through legacy roadblocks, and work tirelessly to solve complex problems and produce tangible results.</p>
<p>
The primary objective of the Product Manager is to build and deploy innovative products, features, and business ideas as part of the on-going re-design and development of our eCommerce/consumer web experience.&nbsp; Working closely with a cross-functional team (developers, marketers, creative, etc.) the Product manager will help define the strategy and vision for a subset of our clubs, and then own development and execution of the clubs&#39; product roadmap.&nbsp; On a day-to-day basis,&nbsp; Product Managers will drive ideas from conception through deployment (via the product roadmap), build marketing plans and initiatives to attract and engage users, test and identify viable business models, define metrics for monitoring performance and defining success, manage strategic projects/relationships, and drive overall business performance.&nbsp; A successful candidate will be highly analytical, customer-focused, data-driven, and possess a passion for media products (books, music, video). He or she will also have a proven track record of taking on end-to-end ownership and delivering results in a face-paced, time-constrained business environment.</p>
<p>
<strong>You Should Be Prepared to...</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Understand and define user needs and behaviors through experience, market research, customer data, and product testing.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Develop the strategy for how your clubs&#39; web products (site, mobile, social, email) will serve the previously defined user needs. Build and manage the product roadmap to execute on this strategy. &nbsp; &nbsp;</li>
<li>
Own and drive various product features and initiatives through full lifecycle development-- from ideation to launch to on-going iteration and testing.</li>
<li>
Work with developers and UI designers to define business/functional requirements and develop high-level wireframes and prototypes. &nbsp;</li>
<li>
